+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RCi4fGfoQcC4LbpkfcRoQc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Summary\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Project Name:** bench-ssg-toolkit  \n**Description:** SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Type:** ES Module (TypeScript)\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/                    # Build engine and core types\n│   │   ├── engine.ts            # BuildEngine class\n│   │   ├── types.ts             # Type definitions\n│   │   ├── templates.ts         # Template factory functions\n│   │   └── index.ts             # Exports\n│   └── plugins/                 # Plugin implementations (directory exists, files not yet examined)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts             # Core engine tests\n│   └── plugins/                 # Plugin-specific tests\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. src/core/ Directory Details\n\n#### **types.ts** - Core Type Definitions\n\nDefines the fundamental interfaces:\n\n1. **SiteConfig** - Configuration object with:\n   - `title`: string\n   - `baseUrl`: string\n   - `outputDir`: string\n   - `contentDir`: string\n   - `templateDir`: string\n\n2. **ContentFile** - Represents a content piece with:\n   - `slug`: string\n   - `title`: string\n   - `content`: string (raw markdown or HTML)\n   - `metadata`: Record<string, unknown>\n   - `date?`: optional string\n   - `tags?`: optional string[]\n   - `template?`: optional string\n\n3. **BuildContext** - Shared state during build process:\n   - `config`: SiteConfig\n   - `files`: ContentFile[]\n   - `output`: Map<string, string> (output path -> rendered content)\n   - `assets`: Map<string, Buffer> (output path -> binary data)\n   - `data`: Map<string, unknown> (shared plugin data store)\n\n4. **PluginHooks** - Optional hooks plugins can implement:\n   - `beforeBuild?(ctx: BuildContext)`: Runs before processing\n   - `transformContent?(file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext)`: Transforms individual files\n   - `afterBuild?(ctx: BuildContext)`: Runs after processing\n\n5. **Plugin** - Interface for plugins:\n   - `name`: string\n   - `version`: string\n   - `dependencies`: string[] (names of plugins this depends on)\n   - `hooks`: PluginHooks\n\n6. **Template** - Rendering template:\n   - `name`: string\n   - `render(content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>)`: string\n\n#### **engine.ts** - BuildEngine Class\n\nThe core orchestration class that:\n- Manages plugin and template registration\n- Resolves plugin execution order using **topological sort (DAG)**\n- Executes the build process in three phases:\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n1. **registerPlugin(plugin)** - Add a plugin to the engine\n2. **registerTemplate(template)** - Add a template\n3. **resolvePluginOrder()** - Topological sort with validation:\n   - Detects circular dependencies and throws `Error: Circular dependency detected`\n   - Detects missing dependencies and throws `Error: Missing dependency`\n   - Returns plugins in correct execution order\n\n4. **build(files)** - Main build orchestration:\n   - **Phase 1 (beforeBuild):** Run all `beforeBuild` hooks in plugin order\n   - **Phase 2 (transformContent):** Apply `transformContent` hooks to each file sequentially through all plugins\n   - **Phase 3 (Rendering):** Render files through templates, generating output in `ctx.output` map\n   - **Phase 4 (afterBuild):** Run all `afterBuild` hooks in plugin order\n   - Returns fully populated `BuildContext`\n\n#### **templates.ts** - Template Factories\n\nTwo built-in templates:\n\n1. **createDefaultTemplate()** - Generates full HTML page:\n   ```html\n   <!DOCTYPE html>\n   <html>\n   <head>\n     <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n   </head>\n   <body>\n     <article>\n       <h1>${title}</h1>\n       ${date ? `<time>${date}</time>` : ''}\n       <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n     </article>\n   </body>\n   </html>\n   ```\n\n2. **createListTemplate()** - For list pages:\n   ```html\n   <!DOCTYPE html>\n   <html>\n   <head>...</head>\n   <body>\n     <h1>${title}</h1>\n     <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n   </body>\n   </html>\n   ```\n\n#### **index.ts** - Exports\n\nExports:\n- `BuildEngine` (class)\n- `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate` (functions)\n- All types from types.ts\n\n---\n\n### 3. tests/core.test.ts - Core Engine Tests\n\n**17 comprehensive tests** covering:\n\n1. **Plugin Registration:**\n   - Registers plugins and retrieves them\n\n2. **Template Registration:**\n   - Registers templates and retrieves them\n\n3. **Build Process:**\n   - Default template rendering with HTML structure\n   - List template rendering\n   - Raw content output when no template matches\n   - Empty file lists\n\n4. **Plugin Hooks:**\n   - `beforeBuild` hook execution\n   - `transformContent` hook execution with file mutation\n   - `afterBuild` hook execution\n   - Multiple plugins' `transformContent` in order (chaining)\n\n5. **Dependency Resolution:**\n   - Executes plugins in correct dependency order\n   - Throws on circular dependencies (A→B→A)\n   - Throws on missing dependencies\n\n6. **Build Context:**\n   - Shared `data` store accessible across plugins\n   - File metadata retention through build\n   - Date and tags preservation\n\n7. **Edge Cases:**\n   - Empty file lists produce empty output\n\n**Test Helpers:**\n- `makeFile()` - Creates ContentFile with defaults\n- `makePlugin()` - Creates Plugin with defaults\n\n---\n\n### 4. tests/plugins/ - Plugin Test Files\n\n#### **markdown-ext.test.ts** - Markdown Processing Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for markdown-to-HTML conversion:\n- Basic markdown: headers, bold text\n- Footnotes with `[^1]` syntax rendering\n- Footnote section generation at content bottom\n- Container admonitions: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip`\n- HTML preservation in content\n- Empty content handling\n\nExpected behaviors:\n- Converts `# Hello` to `<h1>Hello</h1>`\n- Converts `**bold**` to `<strong>bold</strong>`\n- Converts `[^1]: footnote` to rendered footnote with `<sup>` links\n- Converts `:::note ... :::` to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n\n#### **syntax-highlight.test.ts** - Code Highlighting Plugin\n\n**9 tests** for syntax highlighting:\n- Adds language class to code blocks: `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n- Adds `data-language` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Handles code blocks without language specification\n- Adds `highlighted` class to processed blocks\n- Preserves code content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Ignores inline `<code>` tags (doesn't modify them)\n\nExpected patterns:\n- `<pre><code class=\"language-js\">` → adds `data-language=\"js\"` and `highlighted` class\n- `<code>inline</code>` → left untouched\n\n#### **taxonomy.test.ts** - Tag/Category Plugin\n\n**9 tests** for building taxonomies:\n- Builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` from file tags\n- Generates tag listing pages in `ctx.output`\n- Handles files without tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Case-normalizes tags to lowercase (JavaScript → javascript)\n- Generates `tags/${tag}.html` pages listing all files with that tag\n- Stores tag map in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n- Handles empty file lists\n\nPlugin flow:\n- `beforeBuild`: Build tag index from all files\n- `afterBuild`: Generate tag pages as HTML output\n\n#### **asset-pipeline.test.ts** - Asset URL Rewriting Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for asset path handling:\n- Rewrites relative image URLs: `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n- Rewrites relative link URLs: `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged: `https://cdn.example.com/...` untouched\n- Generates asset manifest in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n- Tracks discovered assets: `{ assets: ['photo.jpg', ...] }`\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Doesn't double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\nBehavior:\n- Transforms: `<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">` → `<img src=\"/assets/photo.jpg\">`\n- Skips: `<img src=\"https://...\">`\n- Skips: `<img src=\"/assets/...\">`\n\n#### **rss-feed.test.ts** - RSS Feed Generation Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for RSS 2.0 feed output:\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML with proper structure\n- Includes HTML content in CDATA sections\n- Includes category tags from taxonomy plugin data\n- Uses channel title from `config.title`\n- Sorts items by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates gracefully\n- Uses `baseUrl` from config for links\n- Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n\nRSS structure:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<rss version=\"2.0\">\n  <channel>\n    <title>${config.title}</title>\n    <link>${config.baseUrl}</link>\n    <item>\n      <title>Post Title</title>\n      <link>${baseUrl}/slug.html</link>\n      <pubDate>${date}</pubDate>\n      <category>${tag}</category>\n      <description><![CDATA[${content}]]></description>\n    </item>\n  </channel>\n</rss>\n```\n\n#### **search-index.test.ts** - Search Index Generation Plugin\n\n**7 tests** for JSON search index:\n- Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n- Index entries contain: `slug`, `title`, `content` (plain text)\n- Strips HTML tags from indexed content\n- Includes code blocks in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists (empty array)\n- Valid JSON output\n- Includes `tags` array if present on file\n\nIndex entry format:\n```json\n{\n  \"slug\": \"my-post\",\n  \"title\": \"My Post\",\n  \"content\": \"plain text without HTML tags\",\n  \"tags\": [\"js\", \"web\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### **sitemap.test.ts** - XML Sitemap Generation Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for sitemap generation:\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- Includes all content page URLs from `ctx.output`\n- Includes taxonomy tag page URLs from `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n- Includes `feed.xml` URL if present\n- Uses `baseUrl` from config for full URLs\n- Valid XML structure (declarations, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`)\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\nSitemap format:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"...\">\n  <url>\n    <loc>${baseUrl}/${path}</loc>\n  </url>\n</urlset>\n```\n\n#### **dev-server.test.ts** - Development Server Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for dev server configuration:\n- Stores config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n- Includes port setting (default: 3000)\n- Includes asset routes from `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n- Includes search index path (`/search-index.json`)\n- Includes content routes for each output file\n- Default port is 3000\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\nConfig structure:\n```typescript\n{\n  port: 3000,\n  routes: [\n    { path: string; handler: 'static' | 'asset' }\n  ],\n  assetPaths: string[],\n  searchIndexPath: string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Plugin Interface (from types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;                          // Unique plugin identifier\n  version: string;                       // Semantic version\n  dependencies: string[];                // Array of plugin names this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;                    // Hook implementations\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Design Patterns:**\n- **DAG-based Dependency Resolution:** Plugins declare dependencies; engine performs topological sort\n- **Async/Sync Flexibility:** All hooks support both async and sync implementations\n- **Shared Data Store:** `ctx.data` allows plugins to communicate state (taxonomy, assets, server config, etc.)\n- **Three-Phase Execution:**\n  1. `beforeBuild`: Setup/aggregation phase\n  2. `transformContent`: File-by-file transformation phase\n  3. `afterBuild`: Output generation/finalization phase\n\n---\n\n### 6. package.json - Dependencies and Scripts\n\n**Scripts:**\n```json\n{\n  \"build\": \"tsc\",                    // Compile TypeScript\n  \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",      // Lint code\n  \"test\": \"vitest run\"               // Run tests\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `express` (^5.2.1) - Web server framework\n- `marked` (^17.0.2) - Markdown parser\n- `@types/express` (^5.0.6) - Express type definitions\n- `@types/marked` (^5.0.2) - Marked type definitions\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- `typescript` (^5.9.3) - TypeScript compiler\n- `vitest` (^2.1.9) - Test runner\n- `eslint` (^8.57.1) - Linter\n- `@typescript-eslint/parser` (^7.18.0)\n- `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` (^7.18.0)\n\n---\n\n### Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **Plugin System Architecture:**\n   - Uses directed acyclic graph (DAG) for dependency management\n   - Plugins are composable, with each contributing specific functionality\n   - Communication through shared context and data store\n\n2. **Build Pipeline:**\n   - Three-phase execution ensures proper ordering of transformations\n   - Plugins can't directly modify other files; they work on single files at a time\n   - Output is collected in maps for file system writing later\n\n3. **Test Coverage:**\n   - 79 comprehensive tests covering core engine and 8 different plugins\n   - Each plugin test validates its specific transformations and integrations\n   - Tests validate both happy paths and edge cases\n\n4. **Design Patterns:**\n   - Factory functions for creating templates and plugins\n   - Dependency injection through constructor parameters\n   - Functional composition through hooks system"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5b8b80 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36642\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 44098</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49516ca0-6110-4ce2-8417-b08fb2364615","uuid":"09e1af6f-7327-44e3-b55e-c89c652a46bd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to understand:\n1. The overall structure of the project\n2. The contents of src/core/ (build engine, types, templates)\n3. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n4. The plugin test files in tests/plugins/\n5. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n6. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nPlease read all relevant files and provide a comprehensive summary.","agentId":"a5b8b80","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Summary\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Project Name:** bench-ssg-toolkit  \n**Description:** SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Type:** ES Module (TypeScript)\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/                    # Build engine and core types\n│   │   ├── engine.ts            # BuildEngine class\n│   │   ├── types.ts             # Type definitions\n│   │   ├── templates.ts         # Template factory functions\n│   │   └── index.ts             # Exports\n│   └── plugins/                 # Plugin implementations (directory exists, files not yet examined)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts             # Core engine tests\n│   └── plugins/                 # Plugin-specific tests\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. src/core/ Directory Details\n\n#### **types.ts** - Core Type Definitions\n\nDefines the fundamental interfaces:\n\n1. **SiteConfig** - Configuration object with:\n   - `title`: string\n   - `baseUrl`: string\n   - `outputDir`: string\n   - `contentDir`: string\n   - `templateDir`: string\n\n2. **ContentFile** - Represents a content piece with:\n   - `slug`: string\n   - `title`: string\n   - `content`: string (raw markdown or HTML)\n   - `metadata`: Record<string, unknown>\n   - `date?`: optional string\n   - `tags?`: optional string[]\n   - `template?`: optional string\n\n3. **BuildContext** - Shared state during build process:\n   - `config`: SiteConfig\n   - `files`: ContentFile[]\n   - `output`: Map<string, string> (output path -> rendered content)\n   - `assets`: Map<string, Buffer> (output path -> binary data)\n   - `data`: Map<string, unknown> (shared plugin data store)\n\n4. **PluginHooks** - Optional hooks plugins can implement:\n   - `beforeBuild?(ctx: BuildContext)`: Runs before processing\n   - `transformContent?(file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext)`: Transforms individual files\n   - `afterBuild?(ctx: BuildContext)`: Runs after processing\n\n5. **Plugin** - Interface for plugins:\n   - `name`: string\n   - `version`: string\n   - `dependencies`: string[] (names of plugins this depends on)\n   - `hooks`: PluginHooks\n\n6. **Template** - Rendering template:\n   - `name`: string\n   - `render(content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>)`: string\n\n#### **engine.ts** - BuildEngine Class\n\nThe core orchestration class that:\n- Manages plugin and template registration\n- Resolves plugin execution order using **topological sort (DAG)**\n- Executes the build process in three phases:\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n1. **registerPlugin(plugin)** - Add a plugin to the engine\n2. **registerTemplate(template)** - Add a template\n3. **resolvePluginOrder()** - Topological sort with validation:\n   - Detects circular dependencies and throws `Error: Circular dependency detected`\n   - Detects missing dependencies and throws `Error: Missing dependency`\n   - Returns plugins in correct execution order\n\n4. **build(files)** - Main build orchestration:\n   - **Phase 1 (beforeBuild):** Run all `beforeBuild` hooks in plugin order\n   - **Phase 2 (transformContent):** Apply `transformContent` hooks to each file sequentially through all plugins\n   - **Phase 3 (Rendering):** Render files through templates, generating output in `ctx.output` map\n   - **Phase 4 (afterBuild):** Run all `afterBuild` hooks in plugin order\n   - Returns fully populated `BuildContext`\n\n#### **templates.ts** - Template Factories\n\nTwo built-in templates:\n\n1. **createDefaultTemplate()** - Generates full HTML page:\n   ```html\n   <!DOCTYPE html>\n   <html>\n   <head>\n     <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n   </head>\n   <body>\n     <article>\n       <h1>${title}</h1>\n       ${date ? `<time>${date}</time>` : ''}\n       <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n     </article>\n   </body>\n   </html>\n   ```\n\n2. **createListTemplate()** - For list pages:\n   ```html\n   <!DOCTYPE html>\n   <html>\n   <head>...</head>\n   <body>\n     <h1>${title}</h1>\n     <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n   </body>\n   </html>\n   ```\n\n#### **index.ts** - Exports\n\nExports:\n- `BuildEngine` (class)\n- `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate` (functions)\n- All types from types.ts\n\n---\n\n### 3. tests/core.test.ts - Core Engine Tests\n\n**17 comprehensive tests** covering:\n\n1. **Plugin Registration:**\n   - Registers plugins and retrieves them\n\n2. **Template Registration:**\n   - Registers templates and retrieves them\n\n3. **Build Process:**\n   - Default template rendering with HTML structure\n   - List template rendering\n   - Raw content output when no template matches\n   - Empty file lists\n\n4. **Plugin Hooks:**\n   - `beforeBuild` hook execution\n   - `transformContent` hook execution with file mutation\n   - `afterBuild` hook execution\n   - Multiple plugins' `transformContent` in order (chaining)\n\n5. **Dependency Resolution:**\n   - Executes plugins in correct dependency order\n   - Throws on circular dependencies (A→B→A)\n   - Throws on missing dependencies\n\n6. **Build Context:**\n   - Shared `data` store accessible across plugins\n   - File metadata retention through build\n   - Date and tags preservation\n\n7. **Edge Cases:**\n   - Empty file lists produce empty output\n\n**Test Helpers:**\n- `makeFile()` - Creates ContentFile with defaults\n- `makePlugin()` - Creates Plugin with defaults\n\n---\n\n### 4. tests/plugins/ - Plugin Test Files\n\n#### **markdown-ext.test.ts** - Markdown Processing Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for markdown-to-HTML conversion:\n- Basic markdown: headers, bold text\n- Footnotes with `[^1]` syntax rendering\n- Footnote section generation at content bottom\n- Container admonitions: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip`\n- HTML preservation in content\n- Empty content handling\n\nExpected behaviors:\n- Converts `# Hello` to `<h1>Hello</h1>`\n- Converts `**bold**` to `<strong>bold</strong>`\n- Converts `[^1]: footnote` to rendered footnote with `<sup>` links\n- Converts `:::note ... :::` to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n\n#### **syntax-highlight.test.ts** - Code Highlighting Plugin\n\n**9 tests** for syntax highlighting:\n- Adds language class to code blocks: `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n- Adds `data-language` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Handles code blocks without language specification\n- Adds `highlighted` class to processed blocks\n- Preserves code content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Ignores inline `<code>` tags (doesn't modify them)\n\nExpected patterns:\n- `<pre><code class=\"language-js\">` → adds `data-language=\"js\"` and `highlighted` class\n- `<code>inline</code>` → left untouched\n\n#### **taxonomy.test.ts** - Tag/Category Plugin\n\n**9 tests** for building taxonomies:\n- Builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` from file tags\n- Generates tag listing pages in `ctx.output`\n- Handles files without tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Case-normalizes tags to lowercase (JavaScript → javascript)\n- Generates `tags/${tag}.html` pages listing all files with that tag\n- Stores tag map in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n- Handles empty file lists\n\nPlugin flow:\n- `beforeBuild`: Build tag index from all files\n- `afterBuild`: Generate tag pages as HTML output\n\n#### **asset-pipeline.test.ts** - Asset URL Rewriting Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for asset path handling:\n- Rewrites relative image URLs: `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n- Rewrites relative link URLs: `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged: `https://cdn.example.com/...` untouched\n- Generates asset manifest in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n- Tracks discovered assets: `{ assets: ['photo.jpg', ...] }`\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Doesn't double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\nBehavior:\n- Transforms: `<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">` → `<img src=\"/assets/photo.jpg\">`\n- Skips: `<img src=\"https://...\">`\n- Skips: `<img src=\"/assets/...\">`\n\n#### **rss-feed.test.ts** - RSS Feed Generation Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for RSS 2.0 feed output:\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML with proper structure\n- Includes HTML content in CDATA sections\n- Includes category tags from taxonomy plugin data\n- Uses channel title from `config.title`\n- Sorts items by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates gracefully\n- Uses `baseUrl` from config for links\n- Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n\nRSS structure:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<rss version=\"2.0\">\n  <channel>\n    <title>${config.title}</title>\n    <link>${config.baseUrl}</link>\n    <item>\n      <title>Post Title</title>\n      <link>${baseUrl}/slug.html</link>\n      <pubDate>${date}</pubDate>\n      <category>${tag}</category>\n      <description><![CDATA[${content}]]></description>\n    </item>\n  </channel>\n</rss>\n```\n\n#### **search-index.test.ts** - Search Index Generation Plugin\n\n**7 tests** for JSON search index:\n- Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n- Index entries contain: `slug`, `title`, `content` (plain text)\n- Strips HTML tags from indexed content\n- Includes code blocks in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists (empty array)\n- Valid JSON output\n- Includes `tags` array if present on file\n\nIndex entry format:\n```json\n{\n  \"slug\": \"my-post\",\n  \"title\": \"My Post\",\n  \"content\": \"plain text without HTML tags\",\n  \"tags\": [\"js\", \"web\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### **sitemap.test.ts** - XML Sitemap Generation Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for sitemap generation:\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- Includes all content page URLs from `ctx.output`\n- Includes taxonomy tag page URLs from `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n- Includes `feed.xml` URL if present\n- Uses `baseUrl` from config for full URLs\n- Valid XML structure (declarations, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`)\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\nSitemap format:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"...\">\n  <url>\n    <loc>${baseUrl}/${path}</loc>\n  </url>\n</urlset>\n```\n\n#### **dev-server.test.ts** - Development Server Plugin\n\n**8 tests** for dev server configuration:\n- Stores config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n- Includes port setting (default: 3000)\n- Includes asset routes from `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n- Includes search index path (`/search-index.json`)\n- Includes content routes for each output file\n- Default port is 3000\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\nConfig structure:\n```typescript\n{\n  port: 3000,\n  routes: [\n    { path: string; handler: 'static' | 'asset' }\n  ],\n  assetPaths: string[],\n  searchIndexPath: string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Plugin Interface (from types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;                          // Unique plugin identifier\n  version: string;                       // Semantic version\n  dependencies: string[];                // Array of plugin names this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;                    // Hook implementations\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Design Patterns:**\n- **DAG-based Dependency Resolution:** Plugins declare dependencies; engine performs topological sort\n- **Async/Sync Flexibility:** All hooks support both async and sync implementations\n- **Shared Data Store:** `ctx.data` allows plugins to communicate state (taxonomy, assets, server config, etc.)\n- **Three-Phase Execution:**\n  1. `beforeBuild`: Setup/aggregation phase\n  2. `transformContent`: File-by-file transformation phase\n  3. `afterBuild`: Output generation/finalization phase\n\n---\n\n### 6. package.json - Dependencies and Scripts\n\n**Scripts:**\n```json\n{\n  \"build\": \"tsc\",                    // Compile TypeScript\n  \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",      // Lint code\n  \"test\": \"vitest run\"               // Run tests\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `express` (^5.2.1) - Web server framework\n- `marked` (^17.0.2) - Markdown parser\n- `@types/express` (^5.0.6) - Express type definitions\n- `@types/marked` (^5.0.2) - Marked type definitions\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- `typescript` (^5.9.3) - TypeScript compiler\n- `vitest` (^2.1.9) - Test runner\n- `eslint` (^8.57.1) - Linter\n- `@typescript-eslint/parser` (^7.18.0)\n- `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` (^7.18.0)\n\n---\n\n### Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **Plugin System Architecture:**\n   - Uses directed acyclic graph (DAG) for dependency management\n   - Plugins are composable, with each contributing specific functionality\n   - Communication through shared context and data store\n\n2. **Build Pipeline:**\n   - Three-phase execution ensures proper ordering of transformations\n   - Plugins can't directly modify other files; they work on single files at a time\n   - Output is collected in maps for file system writing later\n\n3. **Test Coverage:**\n   - 79 comprehensive tests covering core engine and 8 different plugins\n   - Each plugin test validates its specific transformations and integrations\n   - Tests validate both happy paths and edge cases\n\n4. **Design Patterns:**\n   - Factory functions for creating templates and plugins\n   - Dependency injection through constructor parameters\n   - Functional composition through hooks system"}],"totalDurationMs":44098,"totalTokens":36642,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":506,"cache_read_input_tokens":32208,"output_tokens":3922,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":506,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
